031/**
032 * Parses UON (a notation for URL-encoded query parameter values) text into POJO models.
033 *
034 * <h5 class='topic'>Media types</h5>
035 * <p>
036 * Handles <c>Content-Type</c> types:  <bc>text/uon</bc>
037 *
038 * <h5 class='topic'>Description</h5>
039 * <p>
040 * This parser uses a state machine, which makes it very fast and efficient.
041 *
042 * <h5 class='section'>Notes:</h5><ul>
043 *    <li class='note'>This class is thread safe and reusable.
044 * </ul>
045 *
046 * <h5 class='section'>See Also:</h5><ul>
047 *    <li class='link'><a class="doclink" href="https://juneau.apache.org/docs/topics/UonBasics">UON Basics</a>
048
049 * </ul>
050 */
051public class UonParser extends ReaderParser implements HttpPartParser, UonMetaProvider {
052
053   //-------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
054   // Static
055   //-------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
056
057   /** Reusable instance of {@link UonParser}, all default settings. */
058   public static final UonParser DEFAULT = new UonParser(create());
059
060   /** Reusable instance of {@link UonParser} with decodeChars set to true. */
061   public static final UonParser DEFAULT_DECODING = new UonParser.Decoding(create());
062
063   /**
064    * Creates a new builder for this object.
065    *
066    * @return A new builder.
067    */
068   public static Builder create() {
069      return new Builder();
070   }

157      /**
158       * Decode <js>"%xx"</js> sequences.
159       *
160       * <p>
161       * When enabled, URI encoded characters will be decoded.  Otherwise it's assumed that they've already been decoded
162       * before being passed to this parser.
163       *
164       * <h5 class='section'>Example:</h5>
165       * <p class='bjava'>
166       *    <jc>// Create a decoding UON parser.</jc>
167       *    ReaderParser <jv>parser</jv> = UonParser.
168       *       .<jsm>create</jsm>()
169       *       .decoding()
170       *       .build();
171       *
172       *  <jc>// Produces: ["foo bar", "baz quz"].</jc>
173       *    String[] <jv>foo</jv> = <jv>parser</jv>.parse(<js>"@(foo%20bar,baz%20qux)"</js>, String[].<jk>class</jk>);
174       * </p>
175       *
176       * @return This object.
177       */
178      @FluentSetter
179      public Builder decoding() {
180         return decoding(true);
181      }
182
183      /**
184       * Same as {@link #decoding()} but allows you to explicitly specify the value.
185       *
186       * @param value The value for this setting.
187       * @return This object.
188       */
189      @FluentSetter
190      public Builder decoding(boolean value) {
191         decoding = value;
192         return this;
193      }
194
195      /**
196       * Validate end.
197       *
198       * <p>
199       * When enabled, after parsing a POJO from the input, verifies that the remaining input in
200       * the stream consists of only comments or whitespace.
201       *
202       * <h5 class='section'>Example:</h5>
203       * <p class='bjava'>
204       *    <jc>// Create a parser using strict mode.</jc>
205       *    ReaderParser <jv>parser</jv> = UonParser.
206       *       .<jsm>create</jsm>()
207       *       .validateEnd()
208       *       .build();
209       *
210       *    <jc>// Should fail because input has multiple POJOs.</jc>
211       *    String <jv>in</jv> = <js>"(foo=bar)(baz=qux)"</js>;
212       *    MyBean <jv>myBean</jv> = <jv>parser</jv>.parse(<jv>in</jv>, MyBean.<jk>class</jk>);
213       * </p>
214       *
215       * @return This object.
216       */
217      @FluentSetter
218      public Builder validateEnd() {
219         return validateEnd(true);
220      }
221
222      /**
223       * Same as {@link #validateEnd()} but allows you to explicitly specify the value.
224       *
225       * @param value The value for this setting.
226       * @return This object.
227       */
228      @FluentSetter
229      public Builder validateEnd(boolean value) {
230         validateEnd = value;
231         return this;
232      }

783    *    Schema information about the part.
784    *    <br>May be <jk>null</jk>.
785    *    <br>Not all part parsers use the schema information.
786    * @param in The input being parsed.
787    * @param toType The POJO type to transform the input into.
788    * @return The parsed value.
789    * @throws ParseException Malformed input encountered.
790    * @throws SchemaValidationException If the input or resulting HTTP part object fails schema validation.
791    */

793      return getPartSession().parse(partType, schema, in, toType);
794   }

839   @Override /* UonMetaProvider */
840   public UonClassMeta getUonClassMeta(ClassMeta<?> cm) {
841      UonClassMeta m = uonClassMetas.get(cm);
842      if (m == null) {
843         m = new UonClassMeta(cm, this);
844         uonClassMetas.put(cm, m);
845      }
846      return m;
847   }
848
849   @Override /* UonMetaProvider */
850   public UonBeanPropertyMeta getUonBeanPropertyMeta(BeanPropertyMeta bpm) {
851      if (bpm == null)
852         return UonBeanPropertyMeta.DEFAULT;
853      UonBeanPropertyMeta m = uonBeanPropertyMetas.get(bpm);
854      if (m == null) {
855         m = new UonBeanPropertyMeta(bpm.getDelegateFor(), this);
856         uonBeanPropertyMetas.put(bpm, m);
857      }
858      return m;
859   }
